meals.title: Poached Eggs with Tomato and Basil Bruschetta

recipe.title: Poached Eggs with Tomato and Basil Bruschetta
instructions: Bring water and vinegar to boil in a saucepan over medium heat
Using a wooden spoon, stir the water creating a whirlpool. Crack the eggs into the water and cook for 3 minutes
Once cooked, use a slotted spoon and remove the eggs from the water and transfer to a bowl. Add the avocado beside the poached eggs
In a separate bowl, combine the tomato, onion, basil, and garlic. Pour the olive oil and vinegar over the top and combine
Transfer the bruschetta into the bowl with the poached eggs
Sprinkle the feta over the bruschetta and season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Serve

recipe.title: Raw Energy Seed Bar
instructions: Soak the prunes in water for 5 minutes. Once the prunes become soft, drain the water. Transfer the soaked prunes to a food processor
Add the oats, almond butter, all the seeds, coconut, rice malt syrup, almonds, water and cinnamon into the food processor. Process until the ingredients are combined and the mixture forms into a ball
Transfer the mixture into a tray and press down firmly with a 2cm thickness in a rectangle
Refrigerate for up to 1-hour to set
Cut the bar into 5 slices. Serve 1 bar and refrigerate the remaining 5 bars to be consumed over the week.

meals.title: Zesty Salmon and Zucchini Noodle Bowl

recipe.title: Zesty Salmon and Zucchini Noodle Bowl
instructions: Heat olive oil in a large fry pan over medium temperature and saute the spring onion and garlic for a few minutes
Mix in the zucchini spirals, basil, chilli, pine nuts, ricotta cheese and cherry tomatoes and cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally
In a separate fry pan over medium heat cook the salmon with lemon juice for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until cooked to liking
Once cooked, mix the salmon through the dish. Season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Divide the meal into two serves. Dish one serving in a bowl and refrigerate the second meal for tomorrow’s leftover

recipe.title: Crunchy Protein Shake
instructions: Add all the ingredients in a protein shaker and shake until combined
Serve

recipe.title: Greek Mezze Board
instructions: Begin marinating the chicken skewers by combining the chicken, lemon juice, oregano and garlic in a bowl. Season with pepper. Cover with glad wrap and refrigerate for half an hour. Once marinated, thread the chicken onto the skewers
Heat a barbecue grill and cook the chicken for 8-10 minutes, turning occasionally to ensure all sides of the chicken are cooked. Once cooked add the skewers onto a serving board
Heat a non-stick fry pan over medium temperature and cook the halloumi for 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Add the halloumi beside the chicken skewers
To make the tzatziki, add the cucumber, yoghurt, garlic, mint and salt in a small bowl. Add the bowl to the mezze board
Add the black olives, tomato and capsicum to the board without combining the ingredients together
Serve

recipe.title: Roast Vegetable Omelette
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking tray with baking paper
Boil water in a small saucepan over medium heat and cook the pumpkin and sweet potato for 8 minutes. Drain the water

Add the pumpkin and sweet potato to the tray and sprinkle rosemary, Himalayan salt, and pepper over the top. Spread the garlic over the top. Bake the pumpkin and sweet potato in the oven for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown
Crack eggs in a bowl and whisk vigorously
Heat olive oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and saute the onion and mushroom for a few minutes
Pour the egg into the frying pan and cook for a few minutes or until the egg mixture begins to set underneath
Add the roasted pumpkin and sweet potato to the middle of the omelette and sprinkle the feta cheese over the top
Fold one half of the omelette over enclosing the filling
Serve the omelette on a plate
Toast the bread until liking and serve beside the omelette

meals.title: Sweet Potato Hummus and Carrot Sticks

recipe.title: Sweet Potato Hummus and Carrot Sticks
ingredients: 150g uncooked sweet potato, skin removed and chopped
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees. Line a baking tray with baking paper
Place the sweet potato onto the tray and bake in the oven for 20 minutes. Once cooked set aside to cool

In a food processor, add the chickpeas, sweet potato, olive oil, water, lemon juice, tahini, garlic, cumin, and paprika. Process until a smooth consistency is formed. Divide the sweet potato and hummus dip into two serves
Dish one serving of the sweet potato and hummus dip with half of the carrot sticks
Refrigerate the second serve for tomorrow’s leftover

meals.title: Zesty Salmon and Zucchini Noodle Bowl (leftover)

recipe.title: Zesty Salmon and Zucchini Noodle Bowl
Quinoa And Chicken Pilaf
instructions: Heat coconut oil in a large saucepan over medium heat and cook the chicken with onion and garlic for 2 minutes. Mix in the capsicum and carrot and saute for a minute or two
Add the quinoa, water, and green peas and cook for a further 15 minutes or until the chicken is cooked. Season with Himalayan salt and pepper. Remove from the heat.
Divide the meal into two serves
Dish one serving in a bowl and refrigerate the second meal as a leftover

recipe.title: Triple Choc Shake
instructions: Add all the ingredients into a blender and blend until a smooth consistency is formed
Pour the smoothie into a large glass
Serve

recipe.title: Naked Turkey Burrito Bowl
ingredients: 150g canned black beans, rinsed and drained
instructions: Heat olive oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and cook the turkey mince with garlic, cumin, paprika, oregano and chilli powder for 7 minutes or until the turkey is cooked, stirring occasionally. Once cooked remove from the heat
Combine the avocado, lemon juice, Himalayan salt and pepper in a bowl
Divide the cooked turkey mince, avocado smash, shallots, corn, black beans, lettuce, cherry tomatoes and lemon wedge between two bowls without mixing the ingredients together
Serve one bowl and refrigerate the second meal for tomorrow’s lunch

meals.title: Sweet Potato Hummus and Carrot Sticks (leftover)

recipe.title: Sweet Potato Hummus and Carrot Sticks

meals.title: Baked Beans And Avocado On Toast

recipe.title: Baked Beans And Avocado On Toast
ingredients: 250g canned diced tomatoes (no added sugar and salt)
120g canned kidney beans, drained and rinsed
120g canned cannellini beans, drained and rinsed
instructions: Heat coconut oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and saute the onion, carrot, and garlic in the pan for a few minutes
Add the canned tomatoes and beans and season with Himalayan salt and pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes over low-medium heat
Whilst the baked beans are cooking, toast the bread slice and place on a plate
Pour the baked beans over the toast and evenly layer the chopped avocado on top
Serve

recipe.title: Crunchy Protein Shake
instructions: Add all the ingredients in a protein shaker and shake until combined
Serve

recipe.title: Lamb Cutlets with Roasted Vegetables
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees
Line a baking tray with baking paper
Combine the olive oil and garlic in a small bowl
Place the vegetables onto the tray and using a pastry brush rub the garlic oil over the vegetables. Season the vegetables with basil, Himalayan salt, and pepper
Bake the vegetables in the oven for 25-30 minutes or until cooked. Once cooked remove from the oven
Whilst the vegetables are baking, in a bowl marinate the lamb chops with oil, rosemary, garlic, and lemon juice
Heat a barbecue and cook the lamb chops for a few minutes on each side or until cooked to liking
Divide the lamb chops and vegetables between two plates. Dish one serving and refrigerate the second meal for tomorrow’s leftover

meals.title: Lentil Tuna Salad With Tahini Lime Topping

recipe.title: Lentil Tuna Salad With Tahini Lime Topping
instructions: Prepare Tahini Lime Dressing by combining all of the ingredients in a small bowl. Set aside.
Heat coconut oil in a frying pan over a medium to high heat. Add in tuna and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add in kale, peas and lentils and sauté for a further 2-3 minutes.
Add in cumin, coriander and parsley and stir through. Cook for an extra minute, until spices are fragrant.
Transfer half to a bowl for lunch and dollop with half of the Tahini Lime Dressing. Refrigerate remaining portion for tomorrow’s leftovers.

instructions: Add all the ingredients in a protein shaker and shake until combined

recipe.title: Chickpea Cream Rice Cakes
instructions: Add ingredients for Chickpea Cream Cheese to a blender and blend until smooth.
Add half of the chickpeas to a container and refrigerate for tomorrow’s leftovers. Add 3 brown rice cakes to a container for tomorrow’s leftovers.
Spread the remaining Chickpea Cream Cheese over 3 brown rice cakes and serve for today’s snack.

meals.title: Lentil Tuna Salad With Tahini Lime Topping (leftover)

recipe.title: Lentil Tuna Salad With Tahini Lime Topping

meals.title: Cranberry Chicken with Roasted Pumpkin and Green Beans

recipe.title: Cranberry Chicken with Roasted Pumpkin and Green Beans
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a deep baking tray with baking paper
Add the olive oil, rosemary, pinch of Himalayan salt and pepper in a small bowl. Set aside
Place the chicken onto the tray. Using a pastry brush, brush 1/3 of the olive oil over chicken. Bake the chicken in the oven for 15 minutes

After 15 minutes, remove the chicken from the oven and add the pumpkin, green beans and onion. Using the pastry brush, brush remaining olive oil over the top. Bake for a further 20-25 minutes or until cooked to liking

Whilst the chicken and vegetables are baking,  heat a saucepan over low-medium temperature and add the cranberries, honey, water, and orange juice and bring to the boil. Continue stirring and cooking for 8 minutes. Set aside
Divide the chicken, pumpkin and green beans into two meals. Evenly pour the cranberry sauce over each chicken piece
Dish one meal and refrigerate the remaining meal for tomorrow’s leftover

recipe.title: Triple Choc Shake
instructions: Add all the ingredients into a blender and blend until a smooth consistency is formed
Pour the smoothie into a large glass
Serve

meals.title: Grass-fed Steak with Roasted Cauliflower Salad

recipe.title: Grass-fed Steak with Roasted Cauliflower Salad
ingredients: 200g raw grass-fed beef steak, fat removed
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking tray with baking paper
Place the cauliflower on the tray and drizzle olive oil over the top. Season the cauliflower with turmeric, Himalayan salt, and pepper and spread garlic over the top
Bake in the oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Once cooked remove from the heat
Season the steak with garlic, paprika, and coriander
Whilst the cauliflower is baking, heat a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and cook the steak for 3-4 minutes on each side or until cooked to liking. Set aside
Combine the spinach leaves, onion, cauliflower in a bowl. Sprinkle the pomegranate seeds over the top
Drizzle the lemon and olive oil over the salad and combine well
Serve the steak beside the roasted cauliflower salad

meals.title: Cranberry Chicken with Roasted Pumpkin and Green Beans (leftover)

recipe.title: Cranberry Chicken with Roasted Pumpkin and Green Beans
Green Pea and Spinach Omelette
instructions: Crack the eggs into a bowl and whisk vigorously. Season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Heat olive oil in a non-stick fry pan over low temperature and saute the green peas and spinach for 5 minutes
Pour in the egg mixture and cook for a further 6 minutes on medium heat. Flip one half of the omelette over and continue to cook for a few minutes or until the egg sets in the middle
Whilst the omelette is cooking, toast the bread until golden brown
Serve the toast beside the omelette on a plate

recipe.title: Walnut Banana Bread
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking dish with baking paper
Combine the banana, walnuts, protein powder, almond flour, plain flour, baking soda and cinnamon in a bowl
In a separate bowl crack the eggs and whisk. Mix in the vanilla extract, apple cider vinegar, and maple syrup
Pour the liquid ingredients into the bowl of dry ingredients
Transfer the mixture into the baking dish and bake in the oven for 45 minutes or until it’s cooked in the middle. Once cooked remove from the oven and allow to cool for 10 minutes
Slice the banana bread into 5 slices
Serve one slice for a snack and refrigerate the remaining slices to be consumed as leftovers

meals.title: Pumpkin Bites With Lamb And Goats Cheese

recipe.title: Pumpkin Bites With Lamb And Goats Cheese
ingredients: 450g uncooked pumpkin, chopped into bite sizes
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking tray with baking paper. Place the pumpkin on the tray and sprinkle rosemary and Himalayan salt over the top. Bake in the oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Once cooked remove from the oven

Meanwhile, heat coconut oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and cook the lamb with crushed garlic and pepper for 4 minutes on each side or until the lamb is cooked to liking. Once cooked set aside
Combine the baby spinach leaves, onion, tomato and goats cheese in a large bowl
Add the cooked pumpkin and lamb to the salad and mix together
Pour the olive oil and vinegar over the salad and combine well
Divide the meal into two serves. Dish one serving of the pumpkin bites with lamb and goats cheese and refrigerate the second meal for tomorrow’s leftover

recipe.title: Protein Coconut Shake
ingredients: 2 1/2 tbsp. natural protein powder (flavour of your choice)
instructions: Add the protein powder and coconut milk in a protein shaker
Shake vigorously until mixed together
Serve

recipe.title: Salmon and Chives Frittata
instructions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees and prepare your baking dish
Crack the eggs into a bowl and whisk vigorously. Add the chives, turmeric, cumin, paprika, Italian herbs, Himalayan salt, and pepper
Heat olive oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium temperature and saute the spring onion and  zucchini with garlic for 1-2 minutes
Pour the egg mixture into the baking dish
Mix in the cherry tomatoes, zucchini, spring onion, and salmon
Sprinkle the cheese over the top
Bake the frittata in the oven for 30 minutes or until cooked in the center
Slice the frittata into two serves
Dish one serving and refrigerate the leftover frittata for tomorrow’s meal

recipe.title: Peanut Butter Protein Crunch Shake
instructions: Add the banana, ice, almond milk, honey, coconut, protein powder and peanut butter in a blender
Blend until a smooth consistency is formed
Pour the smoothie into a large glass
Sprinkle the buckinis over the top
Serve

recipe.title: Chicken Fingers With Tzatziki
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking tray with baking paper
Crack the egg into a bowl and whisk vigorously
Add the breadcrumbs and plain flour into separate bowls. Add the cumin and paprika to the flour, garlic into the egg mixture and Italian herbs to the breadcrumbs
Coat the chicken breast strips in the plain flour then dip into the egg and press firmly down on the chicken strips coating one side (in that order)
Bake the chicken strips in the oven for 30-40 minutes or until its cooked in the center. After 15 minutes, turn the chicken breast over to cook the other side
Whilst the chicken is baking, combine the yoghurt, cucumber, mint, and garlic in a bowl. Season with Himalayan salt
Divide the tzatziki and chicken fingers into two serves. Dish one serving of the chicken fingers and tzatziki and refrigerate the second serve for tomorrow’s leftover

meals.title: Pumpkin Bites With Lamb And Goats Cheese (leftover)

recipe.title: Pumpkin Bites With Lamb And Goats Cheese
Healthy Protein Brekkie Bowl
instructions: To make the boiled eggs, boil water in a saucepan over medium heat and cook the eggs for 7 minutes. Once cooked, drain the water and rinse the eggs under cold water
To crack the shell, use a spoon and tap the top of the egg. Peel the skin off. Repeat for the remaining eggs
Add the baby spinach leaves, avocado, and boiled eggs into a bowl
Sprinkle the pumpkin seeds over the top. Squeeze lemon over the top and season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Serve

recipe.title: Wellness Chicken Bowl
instructions: Heat coconut oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and cook the chicken with turmeric, garlic and basil for 7 minutes or until the chicken is cooked in the middle, stirring occasionally. Once cooked set aside
In 3 separate bowls evenly divide the cooked chicken, chickpeas, sauerkraut, spinach, pumpkin seeds, and goji berries without mixing the ingredients together
Combine the dressing ingredients and evenly pour over the top
Serve one wellness chicken bowl and refrigerate the remaining meals to be consumed over the next couple of days

meals.title: Ginger Beef with Stir Fried Brown Rice

recipe.title: Ginger Beef with Stir Fried Brown Rice
instructions: Boil 700ml of water in a saucepan over medium temperature and cook the brown rice for 20-25 minutes. Season with Himalayan salt and chili. Set aside
Heat coconut oil in a wok over medium temperature and cook the beef with ginger and garlic for a few minutes
Add the broccoli, onion, snow peas, soy sauce and egg and stir regularly for another 4-5 minutes or until the beef is cooked
Transfer the brown rice to the wok and combine well
Divide the meal into two serves. Serve one and refrigerate the leftover meal for tomorrow’s dinner

recipe.title: Strawberry and Coconut Porridge
instructions: Bring coconut milk to the boil in a saucepan over medium heat and add the oats. Reduce to simmer and cook the oats for 4 minutes or until the porridge thickens. Stir occasionally with a wooden spoon
Stir in the coconut and protein powder and cook for a further minute
Pour the porridge into a serving bowl and add the chopped strawberries on top
Serve

instructions: Add the protein powder and coconut milk in a protein shaker
Shake vigorously until mixed together

recipe.title: Tuna And White Bean Salad
ingredients: 300g canned cannellini beans drained and rinsed
instructions: Add the cannellini beans, tuna, lettuce, onion and tomato to a bowl and combine well
Separately combine the dressing ingredients in a small bowl
Pour the dressing over the salad and mix well. Season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Divide the salad into two serves
Dish one serving of the tuna and white bean salad and refrigerate the leftover meal for tomorrow’s lunch

recipe.title: Almond Butter Strawberries
instructions: Pour the almond butter in a small jar
Dip the strawberries in the almond butter
Serve

meals.title: Peri Peri Chicken, Sweet Potato Wedges and Beans

recipe.title: Peri Peri Chicken, Sweet Potato Wedges and Beans
instructions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking dish with baking paper
Season the chicken with garlic, spices and 5ml of olive oil in a bowl
Add the chicken breast onto the tray and bake in the oven for 5 minutes
Remove the tray from the oven and add the sweet potato wedges to the tray. Drizzle remaining oil and season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Bake in the oven for a further 15 minutes
Remove the tray from the oven and add the green beans to the tray
Continue baking for a further 10-15 minutes or until cooked
Transfer the chicken, sweet potato wedges and green beans to a plate
Serve

Blend until a smooth consistency is formed
Pour the smoothie into a large glass

recipe.title: Broccoli And Parmesan Chips
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking tray with baking paper
Place the broccoli florets on the tray
Drizzle olive oil over the top
Sprinkle parmesan cheese over the broccoli and season with Himalayan salt
Bake the broccoli chips in the oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown and crunchy
Divide the broccoli chips into two serves
Dish one serving in a bowl and refrigerate the second serve for tomorrow’s snack

recipe.title: Protein Coconut Shake

instructions: Add the protein powder and coconut milk in a protein shaker
Shake vigorously until mixed together

recipe.title: Cheesy Stuffed Keto Capsicums
ingredients: 4 (100g) red capsicums, top of capsicum removed
instructions: Pre-heat oven to 180 degrees and line a baking tray with baking paper
Heat olive oil in a non-stick fry pan over medium heat and cook the beef mince with beef spices for 1-2 minutes
Mix in the onion, mushroom, and spinach and continue cooking for 5 minutes. Drain any water from the fry pan
Mix in the slivered almonds
Place the capsicums on the tray. Evenly spoon the mixture into each capsicum and sprinkle the mozzarella cheese over the top
Bake the capsicums in the oven for 20 minutes or until the cheese has melted
Remove the capsicums from the oven. Serve 2 and refrigerate the remaining 2 capsicums for tomorrow’s leftover

recipe.title: Healthy Protein Brekkie Bowl
instructions: To make the boiled eggs, boil water in a saucepan over medium heat and cook the eggs for 7 minutes. Once cooked, drain the water and rinse the eggs under cold water
To crack the shell, use a spoon and tap the top of the egg. Peel the skin off. Repeat for the remaining eggs
Add the baby spinach leaves, avocado, and boiled eggs into a bowl
Sprinkle the pumpkin seeds over the top. Squeeze lemon over the top and season with Himalayan salt and pepper
Serve

recipe.title: Almond Butter Strawberries
instructions: Pour the almond butter in a small jar
Dip the strawberries in the almond butter
Serve

recipe.title: Chicken Oregano Souvlaki
instructions: Marinate the chicken by combining the chicken, oregano, parsley, 1 garlic crushed, olive oil, cumin and paprika in a bowl. Refrigerate for 1/2 an hour to set
Remove the chicken from the fridge and thread the chicken on skewers
Heat a barbecue grill over medium temperature and cook the chicken skewers for 3-4 minutes on each side or until it’s cooked all over and in the middle
Combine the yoghurt, cucumber, mint and 1 garlic clove crushed in a small bowl. Season with Himalayan salt
Place the spinach and tomatoes on a plate. Drizzle balsamic vinegar over the spinach. Place the chicken skewers on top of the spinach bed and drizzle the yoghurt and garlic sauce over the top
Serve
